 <!--
  This example shows how Alexa's "French (FR)" voice synthesizer
  renders strings of vowels at varying pitches, creating a "singing" voice.

  Make sure you select "French (FR)" as your Alexa language
  when testing this example.

  The (approximate) pitch shift percentages for
  the equal tempered (dodecaphonic) scale are as follows:

  1     -33.3%
  2mi   -31%
  2maj  -25%
  3mi   -21%
  3maj  -17%
  4     -11%
  5     +0%
  6mi   +5%
  6maj  +12%
  7mi   +17%
  7maj  +25%
  8     +31%

  Some notes:
  –– <break/> elements help maintain the same pronunciation for every not
    they probably reset some internal state in Alexa's LSTM
  –– certain consonants can be added at the beginning, e.g. 'paaaaaa'

 -->

